09:12.952 --> 09:14.186
What'd he say about the fuckin'
lip?

09:14.186 --> 09:16.522
It's $75 for delivery,
installation and assembly.

09:16.522 --> 09:17.990
Well, you already
fucked up the delivery.

09:17.990 --> 09:19.425
You can sets it up
right heres and, for frees,

09:19.425 --> 09:21.494
we'll let you know what kind of
job you're fuckin' doin'.

09:21.494 --> 09:23.596
We can assemble it here, but let
us know where to carry it.

09:23.596 --> 09:24.897
It'll take thirty seconds.

09:24.897 --> 09:26.866
WAYNE: Yeah, while you bounce it
off 30 fuckin' walls.

09:26.866 --> 09:28.935
The customer's
always right.

09:28.935 --> 09:30.636
DAN: Damn right.
Pitter-patter.

09:30.636 --> 09:33.406
WAYNE: All right,
youse go get sorted.

09:33.406 --> 09:34.974
Dan and I will
finish our beers

09:34.974 --> 09:36.876
and we'll go over
some safety tips.

09:36.876 --> 09:40.112
(Church bell ringing)

09:40.112 --> 09:43.115
Gasp! What are you doing here,
Stewart?! Hi, Roald.

09:43.115 --> 09:44.584
Hi, Glen!
Um, hi, everyone!

09:44.584 --> 09:47.353
Roald!
(Inhales sharply)

09:47.353 --> 09:48.554
Assembled fools...

09:48.554 --> 09:50.323
- (Inhales sharply)
- Don't!

09:50.323 --> 09:51.657
Don't what?

09:51.657 --> 09:53.726
Don't with
the dramatic inhale.

09:53.726 --> 09:55.795
I am here...

09:55.795 --> 09:58.698
because I know...
who did it.

09:58.698 --> 10:00.333
How could you possibly know
anything, Stewart?

10:00.333 --> 10:02.568
You refused to participate
in my bake sale!

10:02.568 --> 10:04.103
I offered my brownies.

10:04.103 --> 10:05.838
I don't care if
it's legal, Stewart;

10:05.838 --> 10:07.506
you will not
sell drugs in my church!

10:07.506 --> 10:08.975
Weed isn't even a drug.

10:08.975 --> 10:12.078
I know Dan's the de facto butt
stuff fella in these parts--

10:12.078 --> 10:14.380
Hey! I like a one
in the two.

10:14.380 --> 10:16.282
I said "fella".

10:16.282 --> 10:18.784
But butt stuff's pretty popular
with the Christian youth.

10:18.784 --> 10:21.220
- Shocker.
- That too.

10:21.220 --> 10:23.089
Basically anything
that doesn't involve

10:23.089 --> 10:25.858
penile/vaginal penetration.

10:25.858 --> 10:27.393
Another way to protect
their virginities.

10:27.393 --> 10:28.394
Li'l life hack.

10:28.394 --> 10:30.262
So, they say we can't have
vaginal intercourse,

10:30.262 --> 10:31.330
but we can--

10:31.330 --> 10:32.732
Fire it up the pooper.

10:32.732 --> 10:35.901
- Really?
- Dance like nobody's watchin'.

10:35.901 --> 10:37.403
To each his or her own.

10:37.403 --> 10:38.504
- Now and then.
- All right!

10:38.504 --> 10:41.841
Enough with these
sidebar conversations. Stewart!

10:41.841 --> 10:44.910
Explain yourself in front of
God, his son Jesus,

10:44.910 --> 10:47.146
and all of his
Idrises Elba!

10:47.146 --> 10:50.416
(Both hissing)

10:50.416 --> 10:52.218
- (Hissing)
- Fine!

10:53.619 --> 10:55.287
I grew up reading
all the classics

10:55.287 --> 10:57.590
of Lord Agatha Christie.

10:57.590 --> 10:59.058
I don't think that's
how that works.

10:59.058 --> 11:00.626
- It's not.
- Confirmed.

11:00.626 --> 11:02.261
- Best friend.
- And... (Sniffing)

11:02.261 --> 11:05.965
...I can sniff out
a murder plot a mile away!

11:05.965 --> 11:09.101
Stewart the most
sophisticated sense of smell.

11:10.336 --> 11:11.704
Got any snooters?

11:11.704 --> 11:12.838
No one was murdered.

11:12.838 --> 11:14.140
- Irregardless!
- Ugh.

11:14.140 --> 11:18.277
Allow me to walk you
through... a scenario.

11:18.277 --> 11:20.279
Gettin' close
to boar chop o'clock.

11:20.279 --> 11:23.949
What brought all of
these strange,

11:23.949 --> 11:27.920
disparate people gathered in
this room together today?

11:27.920 --> 11:32.024
Why these people?
And why...

11:32.024 --> 11:34.293
(Inhales sharply)
...here?

11:34.293 --> 11:35.861
I asked them to help me with
the bake sale

11:35.861 --> 11:37.063
'cause we're pals,
and then some.

11:37.063 --> 11:38.330
STEWART:
Likely story.

11:38.330 --> 11:39.532
BOTH: Likely story.

11:39.532 --> 11:40.633
That's a likely story.

11:40.633 --> 11:41.967
- Likely story.
- That's a likely story!

11:41.967 --> 11:45.004
But what about this one?

11:45.004 --> 11:46.806
(Thunder crashing)

11:48.974 --> 11:53.145
No one likes Glen and no one
supports his church.

11:53.145 --> 11:55.881
GLEN: Stewart, you know I can
still hear you, right?

11:55.881 --> 11:57.550
STEWART:
I posit this!

11:57.550 --> 12:00.686
Because no one really wanted to
help Glen or his God

12:00.686 --> 12:02.655
or any of his Idrises Elba,

12:02.655 --> 12:06.425
everyone pretended to put
their profits in the till,

12:06.425 --> 12:10.362
but instead pocketed the money
and kept it for themselves!

12:10.362 --> 12:15.000
♪

12:16.135 --> 12:17.737
There was no money
to be stolen

12:17.737 --> 12:20.539
because everyone
kept their own profits.

12:20.539 --> 12:22.942
♪

12:22.942 --> 12:24.043
Therefore...

12:24.043 --> 12:26.612
(Thunder crashing)

12:26.612 --> 12:29.014
Roald!

12:29.014 --> 12:31.350
The murderer is...

12:31.350 --> 12:33.886
everyone!

12:33.886 --> 12:35.087
No one was murdered,
Stewart.

12:35.087 --> 12:37.156
But wait, does that mean
you all robbed me?

12:37.156 --> 12:38.657
Me and Him?
Capital H.

12:38.657 --> 12:41.293
Isn't that just the plot of
Murder on the Orient Express?

12:41.293 --> 12:43.295
Oh, love that book,
and the movie.

12:43.295 --> 12:45.231
- Which one?
- David Suchet all the way.

12:45.231 --> 12:48.667
I didn't hate the new one.
What up, Michelle Pfeiffer?

12:48.667 --> 12:49.702
Yew!

12:49.702 --> 12:51.904
- She is a masterpiece.
- Mmm-hmm.

12:51.904 --> 12:53.139
She can still get it.

12:53.139 --> 12:55.407
Any time she wants it.

12:55.407 --> 12:58.744
Any time.

12:58.744 --> 13:03.916
(Laughing) Any... time...
she wants... it.

13:06.352 --> 13:09.688
So, What? You're telling me
that you admit it?

13:09.688 --> 13:13.559
You all robbed me, all at
the same time, all at once.

13:13.559 --> 13:15.795
- I got gang-banged?!
- Of course not, Glen.

13:15.795 --> 13:17.163
Oh my God, Tanis,
I did not mean you.

13:17.163 --> 13:18.230
You would never do
that to me.

13:18.230 --> 13:19.732
You're my best friend
since forever.

13:19.732 --> 13:21.066
Enough!

13:24.904 --> 13:29.408
I did not say that's
what happened!

13:29.408 --> 13:31.744
I posited...

13:31.744 --> 13:35.314
that that's how it
could have happened!

13:35.314 --> 13:37.983
But it didn't.
(Inhales sharply)

13:38.984 --> 13:41.086
Allow me
to walk you through...

13:41.086 --> 13:43.389
another scenario.

13:44.690 --> 13:46.559
Do you know
what docking is?

13:46.559 --> 13:47.993
No.

13:47.993 --> 13:49.595
(Thunder crashing)

13:50.863 --> 13:52.698
Do youse have
a stud finder?

13:52.698 --> 13:55.067
I don't believe that's any of
your fuckin' business.

13:55.067 --> 13:57.203
Okoya suggests fastening
the unit to the wall;

13:57.203 --> 13:58.370
helps prevent it
from tipping.

13:58.370 --> 14:00.139
- Youse gots a stud finders?
- Yeah.

14:00.139 --> 14:01.240
Well, fuckin' point it over
here;

14:01.240 --> 14:02.308
I'll tell ya if it's working.

14:02.308 --> 14:03.642
Everybody's got
a stud finder joke.

14:03.642 --> 14:05.978
I don't remember askin'
how nots to tip stuffs.

14:05.978 --> 14:07.446
Did you want
the stud finder or not?

14:07.446 --> 14:09.481
WAYNE: Well, fuckin' don't need
one; already found 'em.

14:09.481 --> 14:11.016
DAN: You let us worries
about that.

14:11.016 --> 14:13.219
Youse just worries about
righty-tightys, leftys-looseys.

14:13.219 --> 14:14.687
You're getting some nice
furniture here.

14:14.687 --> 14:15.721
DAN:
I can see from here

14:15.721 --> 14:17.489
the hardware's stripped
from screwing it in once.

14:17.489 --> 14:19.091
So, tells me again what we're
gettings heres?

14:19.091 --> 14:21.093
WAYNE: Another Allen key
in the fuckin' junk drawer.

14:21.093 --> 14:22.161
People seem to like it.

14:22.161 --> 14:23.596
Know what else people
seemed to like?

14:23.596 --> 14:24.964
Boy bands.

14:24.964 --> 14:27.666
This silly Swedish furniture
is like boy bands:

14:27.666 --> 14:29.134
it's hot for
a second, sure,

14:29.134 --> 14:31.303
but it's only a matter of time
before you're a joke.

14:31.303 --> 14:32.838
The screws get
stripped pretty easily.

14:32.838 --> 14:33.973
You could holds the thing
together

14:33.973 --> 14:34.974
better with fuckin' flour.

14:34.974 --> 14:36.108
But it's good material
otherwise.

14:36.108 --> 14:37.476
WAYNE:
What is?

14:37.476 --> 14:39.078
GUNNER:
This.

14:39.078 --> 14:41.213
WAYNE: Well,
I could piss a hole in that.

14:41.213 --> 14:43.082
Hey, youse guys ever wonder
what it would feel like

14:43.082 --> 14:44.550
to wear a shirt that
fuckin' fits?

14:44.550 --> 14:47.152
- Tight pants kill sperms.
- I don't want kids.

14:47.152 --> 14:49.021
Well, fuckin' bet they don't
want you either, bud.

14:49.021 --> 14:50.522
We've got a couple of
stud finders in the truck.

14:50.522 --> 14:52.191
- You can have this one.
- All right.

14:52.191 --> 14:54.760
Well, don't point it over here;
it'll fuckin' break right off.

14:54.760 --> 14:57.997
KATY:
Hang on. Glen,

14:57.997 --> 14:59.365
what does the youth group
need money for?

14:59.365 --> 15:01.734
- Katy!
- I've been to youth group

15:01.734 --> 15:03.569
and all youse got
is refreshments.

15:03.569 --> 15:05.070
No more than $20 dollars,

15:05.070 --> 15:07.406
more like $15
if you're cuttin' coupons.

15:07.406 --> 15:08.874
So, where does
the rest of it go?

15:08.874 --> 15:09.909
Ask the Vatican.

15:09.909 --> 15:11.310
If a Girl Guide
or a Boy Scout

15:11.310 --> 15:12.945
comes to the door
selling cookies,

15:12.945 --> 15:14.113
I know where
the money's going -

15:14.113 --> 15:15.314
sendin' kids
camping and whatnot.

15:15.314 --> 15:17.516
Or if a GI Jehovah
comes to the door,

15:17.516 --> 15:18.918
I know where
the money's going -

15:18.918 --> 15:20.319
cancelling Christmas
and whatnot.

15:20.319 --> 15:22.888
But youse
don't go camping

15:22.888 --> 15:24.523
and youse love Christmas.

15:24.523 --> 15:27.092
So, I ask:
what is the money for?

15:27.092 --> 15:30.296
Katy, have you seen the
price of Freshie lately?

15:30.296 --> 15:31.830
Mm, they don't make
that anymore.

15:31.830 --> 15:33.032
Exactly!

15:33.032 --> 15:34.466
You can get all the Freshie
you want on the...

15:34.466 --> 15:36.568
BOTH (Whispering):
Dark web.

15:36.568 --> 15:38.370
Coach!

15:38.370 --> 15:39.805
Hi, Stewart.

15:39.805 --> 15:43.309
You are an emotional
basket case.

15:43.309 --> 15:45.210
Well, I was unware
you felt this way.

15:45.210 --> 15:47.846
You have never recovered from
the death of your wife.

15:47.846 --> 15:49.281
Barb?

15:49.281 --> 15:51.383
We all know
her name, Coach.

15:51.383 --> 15:54.453
Though, come to think of it,
I don't know yours.

15:54.453 --> 15:57.489
- Irregardless!
- (Thunder crashing)

15:58.524 --> 16:02.127
Coach, you're the angriest man
we all know.

16:02.127 --> 16:04.663
And then, no one bought
any of your fruitcake.

16:04.663 --> 16:07.466
That might be enough to
push a man over the edge.

16:07.466 --> 16:11.470
That might be enough to
drive a man to murder!

16:11.470 --> 16:21.480
♪

16:23.816 --> 16:25.284
Ugh.
No one got--

16:25.284 --> 16:28.387
(Thunder crashing)

16:28.387 --> 16:30.689
No one got murdered,
Stewart!

16:30.689 --> 16:32.224
I'm confused.

16:32.224 --> 16:34.193
Is this supposed to be
another Agatha Christie book?

16:34.193 --> 16:35.227
Of course it is.

16:35.227 --> 16:37.329
I don't recognize
this plot at all.

16:37.329 --> 16:39.164
Is it Evil Under The Sun?

16:39.164 --> 16:40.966
- It's not The ABC Murders.
- Ten Little Indians?

16:40.966 --> 16:42.201
- (Inhales sharply)
- She said it.

16:42.201 --> 16:44.169
It's Death on the Nile!

16:44.169 --> 16:45.637
- No, it isn't.
- Yes it is!

16:45.637 --> 16:47.406
Death on the Nile is
about the poor couple

16:47.406 --> 16:49.875
that kills the rich girl
to take her money.

16:49.875 --> 16:51.744
Hastily simplified,
but yes.

16:51.744 --> 16:53.812
Stewart, your Coach theory is
nothing like Death on the Nile.

16:53.812 --> 16:57.449
(Scoffing) It is a very close
approximation.

16:57.449 --> 16:59.051
- It's not.
- Can confirm.

16:59.051 --> 17:00.419
Coach!

17:01.220 --> 17:05.057
What... say... you?

17:05.057 --> 17:07.092
I didn't do that.

17:07.092 --> 17:08.560
(Both scoffing)
What a defence!

17:08.560 --> 17:09.962
- What a defence!
- What a defence!

17:09.962 --> 17:12.231
BOTH: What a defence!
What a defence! What a defence!

17:12.231 --> 17:14.633
I was actually quite happy
no one bought the fruit cake

17:14.633 --> 17:16.435
because I found
that in the pantry

17:16.435 --> 17:18.237
and I don't even know
how long it's been there.

17:18.237 --> 17:20.773
- Coach...
- No, guys,

17:20.773 --> 17:23.142
it's much darker
than that.

17:23.142 --> 17:26.712
I, um... I guess...

17:26.712 --> 17:29.848
a few months ago, I started
hittin' the bottle pretty hard--

17:29.848 --> 17:31.016
Anyhoo!

17:31.016 --> 17:33.385
I don't think
Coach did it, Stewart.

17:33.385 --> 17:36.522
I didn't say that
Coach did it, Rosie.

17:36.522 --> 17:38.690
I said he might
have done it.

17:38.690 --> 17:40.025
No, you said he did it.

17:40.025 --> 17:42.327
I posited!
It was only a posit.

17:42.327 --> 17:45.998
And allow me to...
posit...

17:45.998 --> 17:48.467
one... last...

17:49.868 --> 17:51.637
- (Thunder crashing)
- ...time.

17:51.637 --> 17:53.672
- JENS: All done, gentleman.
- DAN: Gots the times?

17:53.672 --> 17:55.441
- Time to get a watch.
- WAYNE: Don't get lippy.

17:55.441 --> 17:56.742
There's that
fuckin' lips agains.

17:56.742 --> 17:58.811
- It's six o'clock.
- Oh, he's learnin'.

17:58.811 --> 18:00.579
Sure you don't want us to take
this up to the bedroom?

18:00.579 --> 18:02.247
Who said anything
about a bedroom?

18:02.247 --> 18:03.482
Well, they're
bedside tables.

18:03.482 --> 18:04.850
It's just a name, Jennifer.

18:04.850 --> 18:07.152
DAN: They could just as
easily be ends tables.

18:07.152 --> 18:09.354
WAYNE: Could just as easily be
a little table in the kitchen

18:09.354 --> 18:11.423
to put the telephone on,
maybe a little notepad.

18:11.423 --> 18:13.058
DAN: Spend all day haulin'
fuckin' boxes,

18:13.058 --> 18:14.460
you should learn to thinks
outsides of one.

18:14.460 --> 18:15.961
So, you don't want us to take
this inside?

18:15.961 --> 18:17.329
- WAYNE: Sorted.
- Okay.

18:17.329 --> 18:19.865
All right, Dan,
better fuckin' get it inside

18:19.865 --> 18:22.234
before the wind
blows it over.

18:27.239 --> 18:28.740
Your tips.

18:28.740 --> 18:31.210
Hey, thanks.
I didn't see this coming.

18:31.210 --> 18:32.778
- Want another one?
- BOTH: Sure.

18:32.778 --> 18:34.079
Be on time.

18:34.079 --> 18:36.915
(Both laughing)

18:42.287 --> 18:44.256
Now, what are we gonna do
with this piece of shit?

18:44.256 --> 18:45.757
Good Lord...

18:45.757 --> 18:46.758
Christ sake.

18:46.758 --> 18:49.161
This'll be the only time
I offer you a screw.

18:49.161 --> 18:52.297
I'll take it, good buddy.
Alley-oop.

18:52.297 --> 18:54.433
Clearly don't know anything
about Agatha Christie!

18:54.433 --> 18:57.836
(All shouting at once)

18:57.836 --> 18:59.538
Fine!

19:00.405 --> 19:02.541
(Inhales sharply)
Allow for one last--

19:02.541 --> 19:06.245
Last time I tell ya about
the dramatic inhale, skid.

19:08.780 --> 19:10.616
Hey, bitch!

19:13.218 --> 19:16.989
GLEN: Ooh. Ooh.

19:18.724 --> 19:22.961
(Grunting)

19:22.961 --> 19:24.963
Who's the bitch now?

19:26.598 --> 19:28.167
Bravo.

19:28.167 --> 19:30.302
I was getting
hiccups anyway.

19:32.037 --> 19:36.975
Allow one
last theory

19:36.975 --> 19:40.179
because this theory...

19:40.179 --> 19:43.148
is the truth.

19:43.148 --> 19:45.450
(Thunder crashing)

19:45.450 --> 19:49.121
♪

19:49.121 --> 19:52.658
I was hurt
- nay, offended -

19:52.658 --> 19:55.227
when Glen rejected
my offer of baked-baked goods.

19:55.227 --> 19:56.795
ROALD: (Giggling)
Good one, Stewart.

19:56.795 --> 19:59.831
STEWART: Roald!

19:59.831 --> 20:03.402
So, after everyone had packed
up and left the church,

20:03.402 --> 20:06.838
I snuck back in and
stole the money myself!

20:06.838 --> 20:16.848
♪

20:21.086 --> 20:24.089
(Gasping)
But, Stewart...

20:24.089 --> 20:25.390
Yes, Roald?

20:25.390 --> 20:29.595
Why? Why would you do
all of this?

20:29.595 --> 20:32.231
To see if I could
get away with it...

20:32.231 --> 20:36.034
and... I... did.

20:36.034 --> 20:37.502
Curtain!

20:37.502 --> 20:39.071
Curtain couldn't
come soon enough.

20:39.071 --> 20:40.872
Wait just a minute.

20:40.872 --> 20:42.040
Curtain -

20:42.040 --> 20:45.077
that's the name of
the last Hercule Poirot book,

20:45.077 --> 20:47.412
the one where the detective
himself commits the murder

20:47.412 --> 20:49.314
and then kills
himself at the end.

20:49.314 --> 20:50.616
- Exactly.
- Ooh.

20:50.616 --> 20:52.384
Are you gonna kill
yourself now, Stewart?

20:52.384 --> 20:55.520
(Chuckling) More lookin'
at Coach for that.

20:55.520 --> 20:58.023
Stewart, as a man
of the cloth,

20:58.023 --> 20:59.725
I cannot condone suicide.

20:59.725 --> 21:02.361
However, I do recommend
that you repent!

21:02.361 --> 21:04.563
(Hissing)

21:05.797 --> 21:08.100
Nah.

21:08.100 --> 21:09.534
GLEN:
Ugh.

21:11.136 --> 21:13.538
So, how much
is in there, Glen?

21:13.538 --> 21:16.041
Well, if it's all here,
and I certainly hope it is,

21:16.041 --> 21:20.012
then we will have collected
just shy of...

21:20.012 --> 21:23.782
thirty dollars!
And it's all here! Woo-hoo!

21:23.782 --> 21:27.119
We listened to Stewart talk for
what felt like two fiscal weeks

21:27.119 --> 21:29.021
for thirty bucks?

21:29.021 --> 21:30.722
Just shy
of thirty bucks!

21:31.923 --> 21:33.492
And... curtain.

21:33.492 --> 21:35.227
I'd have a beer.

21:35.227 --> 21:36.295
You're going so soon?

21:36.295 --> 21:37.729
I owe my hick
a boar chop supper.

21:37.729 --> 21:39.598
- Ooh! Salt and pepper?
- You got it, girl.

21:39.598 --> 21:40.832
Tell boo I said what's up.

21:40.832 --> 21:41.667
You got it, girl.

21:41.667 --> 21:43.468
GLEN:
But-- but wait.

21:43.468 --> 21:45.037
We just reacquired
all this money.

21:45.037 --> 21:47.873
And what on earth
am I gonna do with it all?

21:47.873 --> 21:49.374
Ask the Vatican!

21:49.374 --> 21:51.276
You know, again, this is not
a Catholic church.

21:51.276 --> 21:53.345
Okay, in the future,
I would pay $50

21:53.345 --> 21:55.480
to not have to
listen to Stewart speak.

21:55.480 --> 21:57.749
Oof. Amen to that.

21:57.749 --> 22:00.218
But...
ba-doop-boop-boop,

22:00.218 --> 22:04.089
I just wanted to thank you
for everything you did today,

22:04.089 --> 22:05.490
bestie.

22:05.490 --> 22:06.558
(Tanis groaning)

22:06.558 --> 22:08.694
So, what's docking?

22:10.829 --> 22:11.997
We can't do it.

22:11.997 --> 22:13.298
Hmm.

22:13.298 --> 22:15.500
Wanna soak?

22:18.870 --> 22:20.205
Not in my pews.

22:20.205 --> 22:22.607
(The Age of Electric "Enya")

22:22.607 --> 22:27.746
♪

22:27.746 --> 22:29.681
- How 'r' ya now?
- Good, 'n you?

22:29.681 --> 22:32.017
You wanna know what, I'm just
gonna come right out and say it:

22:32.017 --> 22:33.385
I'm half cut.

22:33.385 --> 22:36.355
- I'll catch up.
- Good enough.

22:36.355 --> 22:38.657
What smells
like boar chops?

22:38.657 --> 22:40.192
Oh, might be boar chops.

22:40.192 --> 22:41.360
- Might it?
- Or it mightn't.

22:41.360 --> 22:43.328
I thought we established
that I owe you one?

22:43.328 --> 22:45.297
Well, you like
boar chops, right?

22:45.297 --> 22:46.298
Love boar chops.

22:46.298 --> 22:48.233
Well, I made you
boar chops, Rosie.

22:50.669 --> 22:53.071
Guess I'll have to
make up for it after.

22:53.071 --> 22:53.905
WAYNE:
'Kay.

22:53.905 --> 22:56.274
You can wait a
couple hours, right?

22:56.274 --> 22:57.576
(Wayne grumbling)

22:57.576 --> 23:01.346
(Both grumbling)

23:01.346 --> 23:01.847
♪ Hide in
your inner circle ♪

23:04.449 --> 23:05.851
♪ Strength ain't muscle ♪

23:05.851 --> 23:08.387
♪ Whatever makes it better ♪

23:08.387 --> 23:10.021
♪ Hold onto
your pride ♪

23:10.021 --> 23:13.525
♪ In time,
your faith will wither ♪

23:13.525 --> 23:14.760
♪ Fucked up and gone ♪

23:14.760 --> 23:19.364
♪ Hurt won't
live forever ♪

23:19.364 --> 23:26.371
♪

23:26.371 --> 23:28.540
♪ Enya ♪

23:29.674 --> 23:32.310
♪ In your garden ♪

23:32.310 --> 23:35.380
♪ All of your angels gather ♪

23:35.380 --> 23:39.384
♪ Taking you into hiding ♪

23:39.384 --> 23:42.521
♪ Under their wings ♪

23:44.055 --> 23:45.891
♪ Enya ♪

23:47.392 --> 23:49.694
♪ In your saviour ♪

23:49.694 --> 23:52.831
♪ Can you find hope for future ♪

23:52.831 --> 23:56.401
♪ Where all fears and anger ♪

23:56.401 --> 23:58.570
♪ Won't cloud your... ♪
